  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Thread leaks"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use this check to detect threads you create using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "pthread_create(_:_:_:_:)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function without a corresponding call to the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "pthread_join(_:_:)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function. Leaked threads can result in decreased performance and may lead to crashes. Available in Xcode 8 and later.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Leaked-thread-in-C",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Leaked thread in C",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the following example, the code creates a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "thread",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " variable, but doesn’t close it after use:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "void *run(){",
            "    pthread_exit(0);",
            "}",
            "pthread_t thread;",
            "pthread_create(&thread, NULL, run, NULL); // Error: thread leak",
            "sleep(1);"
          ],
          "syntax": "occ",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Solution",
          "level": 4,
          "text": "Solution",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Add a call to the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "pthread_join(_:_:)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "void *run(){",
            "    pthread_exit(0);",
            "}",
            "pthread_t thread;",
            "pthread_create(&thread, NULL, run, NULL);",
            "sleep(1);",
            "pthread_join(thread, NULL); // Correct"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Alternatively, you can create a detached thread by passing the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "PTHREAD_CREATE_DETACHED",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " attribute to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "pthread_create(_:_:_:_:)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", or calling ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "pthread_detach(_:)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " on the thread after creation.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
